  "texts": [
    "Comparing semantic distance to vignettes.",
    "We embedded all reappraisals and vignettes with a MPNet model fine-tuned on a sentence similarity task (https://huggingface.co/sentence- transformers/stsb-mpnet-base-v2) (Song et al., 2020).",
    "MPNet (Song et al., 2020) uses a combination of permutation and masking to improve the model's information about future tokens, and our model of choice was further fine-tuned on the GLUE STSB dataset (\"General Language Understanding",
    "Evaluation\", \"Semantic Textual Similarity Benchmark\" (Cer et al., 2017)), to optimize the close representation of semantic similar texts with respect to human judgement.",
    "This means that the model was trained to predict the similarity of two sentences A and B on a scale from 0 to 5 based on humanlabeled data."
  ],
